description:
The Airtable API can be used to integrate your data in Airtable with any external system. The API closely follows REST semantics, uses JSON to encode objects, and relies on standard HTTP codes to signal operation outcomes.

Please see [https://airtable.com/developers/web/api/introduction](https://airtable.com/developers/web/api/introduction) for more details.

To get started, you'll need to generate a personal access token. There are two ways to do that in Airtable:

1. [https://airtable.com/create/tokens](https://airtable.com/create/tokens) to create a token in Builder Hub. This token is associated to your Airtable user account. Recommended for testing and personal use.
    
2. For Business & Enterprise customers, it's recommended admins create a [service account](https://support.airtable.com/docs/service-accounts-overview) (system user) in the admin panel and a personal access token there.
    

Make sure to account for what [scopes](https://airtable.com/developers/web/api/scopes) each endpoint requires.

After generating your token, update the Variables tab.
